━━━ WHAT TO GENERATE ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Generate between 8 and 15 ADL blocks. Each block must:
  1. Target one specific architectural concern
  2. Use DEFINE SYSTEM at the top to establish namespace context
  3. Contain at least one ASSERT or FOREACH statement
  4. Have a PROMPT field specific enough that an LLM can produce
     compilable ArchUnit or equivalent code from it alone

Cover these concern categories across the full set of blocks:
  - Structural containment: which classes live in which packages
  - Dependency rules: what may and may not depend on what
  - Service boundary isolation: services must not share internals
  - Characteristic enforcement: rules that protect the inferred
    architecture characteristics (latency, isolation, etc.)

━━━ VALID EXAMPLE (payment system) ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  REQUIRES ArchUnit Java library
  DESCRIPTION Payment service must not depend on fraud internals
  PROMPT Based on this pseudo-code, write an ArchUnit test in Java

  DEFINE SYSTEM Payment Platform AS com.payments
    DEFINE SERVICE Payment Service AS payment_service
    DEFINE SERVICE Fraud Service   AS fraud_service

  ASSERT(payment_service has NO DEPENDENCY ON fraud_service CLASSES)

